><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135728?merchant=Amazon" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-pid="46948" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135728?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$9</span> from <span>Amazon</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="b069223e" data-scp="removed"></div></div><p>Among pens designed to reduce writing stress, the <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="reviewIntro" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="46948" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon">Pilot Dr. Grip Center of Gravity</a> is the best we’ve tested. Our testers—including a retired medical professional with arthritis—found the wide grip easy to hold, and this pen had the best balance of softness and firmness.</p><p>What sets this pen apart the most from other ergonomic pens is its weight distribution: It’s balanced closer to the tip, so writing is effortless and requires less pressure.</p><p>The Center of Gravity is also just a great pen in general. Its hybrid ink combines the long-lasting elements of a ballpoint pen with the dark, vibrant lines of a gel pen.</p><p><strong>Style:</strong> ballpoint<br/><strong>Tip width tested:</strong> 1.0 mm<br/><strong>Widths available:</strong> <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46949/174758/4/135738/?merchant=Staples" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Staples" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46949/174758/4/135738/?merchant=Staples" data-vars-store="Staples" data-gtm-context="reviewIntro" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Staples" data-pid="46949" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46949/174758/4/135738/?merchant=Staples">0.7 mm</a> (fine), <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noopener" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="reviewIntro" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="46948" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46948/174757/4/135737/?merchant=Amazon">1.0 mm</a> (medium)<br/><strong>Colors:</strong> black, blue</p><div class="ebb615ab global-cob e1e566ad a9af8aa7 d097cc30" data-scp="callout"><h4 class="d02b79e1 e20b6350" data-scp="callout_label">Also great</h4><div id="callout-intro-5-3" class="fd1ac384" data-scp="callout_item" data-testid="callout" data-pid="5541"><span class="ddf294c5"><div class="fabe3ad3"><div class="e14704b2" role="button" tabindex="0" data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="5541"><span aria-label="Save Product" class="a478f5d2  " data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="5541"></spa