pen</a></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">With its fast-drying ink, this pen is our go-to for everyday writing on any kind of paper.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/200/587/4/35936?merchant=Amazon" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="200" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/200/587/4/35936?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$14</span> from <span>Amazon</span><br/><span>(pack of three)</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>Our testing group agreed with our experts: The <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/200/587/4/78073/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/200/587/4/78073/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_our-pick-uni-ball-jetstream-rt" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="200" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/200/587/4/78073/?merchant=Amazon">Uni-ball Jetstream RT</a> is the best pen for most everyday writing tasks. It’s smoother to write with than nearly any other ballpoint, and its ink flows without blobbing, skipping, feathering, or bleeding through pages. And it dries quickly, without smudging.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p><strong>It’s been a panel favorite for a decade.</strong> Our testers unanimously selected the Jetstream RT as the best ballpoint pen, with two testers choosing it as their favorite pen overall. This has been the case since we made our initial pen recommendations, back in 2013.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>“The Jetstream just feels like such a solid, trusty pen—the ink is dark, it flows well, it’s sturdy, and feels good in the hand,” said Wirecutter’s Janet Towle. “It’s not an <em>exciting</em> pen, but maybe I’m making my peace with that.”</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>Other ballpoint pens we tested, such as the <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46768/174461/4/135749/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46768/174461/4/135749/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_our-pick-uni-ball-jetstream-rt" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="46768" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46768/174461/4/135749/?merchant=Amazon">Zebra Pen F-301</a>, were less expensive, but they were also less comfortable to write with, felt cheap, or inked fainter lines.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 bdfcf243"><figure id="attachment_222197" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image b71ff2c5"><img loading="lazy" alt="A person holding the Uni-ball Jetstream RT." src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024" data-srcset="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024&amp;dpr=1.5 1536w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024&amp;dpr=2 2048w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=980 980w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=980&amp;dpr=1.5 1470w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=980&amp;dpr=2 1960w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=768 768w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=768&amp;dpr=1.5 1152w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=768&amp;dpr=2 1536w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=480 480w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=480&amp;dpr=1.5 720w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=480&amp;dpr=2 960w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320 320w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320&amp;dpr=1.5 480w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-Uni-ball-Jetstream.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320&amp;dpr=2 640w" width="2048" height="1365" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce size-full wp-image-222197"/></div><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> The Uni-Ball Jetstream RT has a soft rubber grip that covers almost the entire pen body.<!-- --> <span class="wp-caption-text wp-caption-credit">Photo: Melanie Pinola</span></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p><strong>Its ink dries quickly and almost never smudges.</strong> You may have been turned off of ballpoint pens in general because their inks aren’t satisfyingly dark, or because they’re not as smooth to write with as other types of pens. The Jetstream RT could change your mind.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>Our testers noted that this pen’s dark ink dried quickly and smudged the least of all the pens we tested. And the Jetstream RT’s ink was the least visible on the other side of a notebook’s page. In our testing, we used the 0.7-mm medium-to-large point size, yet our writing still felt precise.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 bdfcf243"><figure id="attachment_222198" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image b71ff2c5"><img loading="lazy" alt="A writing sample produced with the Uni-ball Jetstream RT." src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-samples-Uni-ball-Jetstream-ballpoint-sample.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-samples-Uni-ball-Jetstream-ballpoint-sample.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024" data-srcset="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-samples-Uni-ball-J