mazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="removed" tabindex="-1" data-pid="46764" data-gtm-context="inline"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/46764/Uni-ball-Signo-RT1_20221207-214934_full.jpeg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Uni-ball Signo RT1" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-pid="46764" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">Uni-ball Signo RT1</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" class="c44f6873" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="A minimalist-looking gel pen for fine-tip lovers" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_title" data-scp="callout_title" data-pid="46764" data-gtm-context="inline">A minimalist-looking gel pen for fine-tip lovers</a></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">This pen has an understated, single-color barrel design. It writes smoothly, with vivid inks and very thin lines.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-pid="46764" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135731?merchant=Amazon" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$14</span> from <span>Amazon</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>The <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135733/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="5" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135733/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_also-great-uni-ball-signo-rt1" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="46764" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46764/182951/4/135733/?merchant=Amazon">Uni-ball Signo RT1</a> is a great option for people who have small handwriting and like to write with dark lines.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p><strong>It writes well and comes in lots of colors.</strong> The RT1 has satisfyingly saturated ink and comes in 0.28-mm, 0.38-mm, and 0.5-mm pen-tip sizes. And in those small pen-tip sizes, the Signo RT1 has more color options than similar pens.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 bdfcf243"><figure id="attachment_222214" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 glob