 or less for a basic pen and $15 or less for a specialty pen (including ergonomic and multicolor models). We also targeted pens that can be purchased at big-box retailers, office-supply stores, or major online vendors, such as Amazon. Following feedback from readers and experts (as well as our own conscience), we also focused on pens that are refillable and therefore more eco-friendly than disposable pens. These pens may seem boring, but they’re meaningful upgrades over giveaway pens and are great for everyday carry (EDC). If you want something a bit fancier, we’ve also included, in our Other good pens section, a few recommendations for nicer-looking or more-distinct (yet still under-$20) pens that you might keep at your desk. And though we love fountain pens, that’s a whole can of worms we’re saving for another time. Here’s a quick primer on a few pen terms you’ll see throughout this guide:  \tFeathering refers to ink bleeding from the edge of letters, versus crisp lettering.  \tBleeding refers to ink coming through to the other side of the paper or even to the next sheet.  \tSkipping refers to ink not consistently connecting lines or letters, particularly when you’re writing in script.  \tSmudging is when the ink smears and the letters you write blur. It’s particularly noticeable if you write left-handed or try to highlight something you just wrote. (Slow-drying inks that typically smudge can even transfer to other paper.)  \tBlotting refers to the pooling of ink in one spot when you’re writing, because the paper hasn’t yet absorbed the ink. When completing evaluations, each tester used every pen to write at least four pages in a notebook filled with paper that works well with all types of ink. Testers considered:  \tInk smoothness: How freely did the ink flow, and how much pressure was needed to write clearly?  \tPrecision and consistency: We looked for pens that create uniform, crisp lines. Was there any smudging, feathering, skipping, or blotting? Did the ink bleed through to another sheet?  \tComfort: For example, how easy was it to grip the pen when writing for an hour at a time? Finally, we asked testers which pen they would buy for themselves or recommend to others, based on the qualities above and the pen’s design and aesthetics.","title":"How we picked and tested","slug":"how-we-picked-and-tested","chapterModifiedDate":null,"chapterPublishedDate":null,"faqs":null,"footnotes":null,"sources":null},{"body":[{"type":"tag","name":"shortcode-caption","attribs":{"id":"attachment_222196","align":"alignnone","width":"2048"},"children":[{"type":"tag","name":"img","attribs":{"class":"alignnone size-full wp-image-222196","src":"https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-6473.jpg","alt":"The best everyday ballpoint pen, the Uni-ball Jetstream RT, shown on a notebook.","width":"2048","height":"1365","noInlineStyles":true,"postType":"review"},"children":[],"dbData":{"productionCDN":true,"source":"wp-content/media/2021/09/pens-2048px-6473.jpg"}},{"data":" ","type":"text"},{"data":" ","type":"comment"}],"dbData":{"credit":"Photo: Michael Hession"}},{"data":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"shortcode-callout","attribs":{"type":"primary","id":"1"},"children":[],"dbData":{"ribbon":"Our pick","callouts":[{"name":"Uni-ball Jetstream RT","title":"The best everyday ballpoint pen","images":{"full":"https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/200/Uni-ball-Jetstream_20190619-154423_full.jpg"},"description":"With its fast-drying ink, this pen is our go-to for everyday writing on any kind of paper.","notGreat":0,"ribbon":"Our pick","pickTypeId":1,"referenceId":35936,"sources":[{"id":587,"price":{"raw":1399,"formatted":"$14"},"order":0,"merchantName":"Amazon","buttonDetails":"(pack of three)","valueAdd":"","availability":"InStock","countryId":"usa","rawUrl":"http://www.amazon.com/uni-ball-Jetstream-Point-Retractable-70877/dp/B002FSZP5A","countryCode":"US","currency":"USD","url":"https://wclink.co/link/200/587/4/35936","